# Unity & C# conventions

Unity Editor version is `2022.3.62f3` LTS. Do not upgrade or change it without an ADR under `docs/02-architecture/adr/`.

## C# style

- Types: `PascalCase` (`MasterclassRecorder`, `GhostHandRenderer`).
- Methods, public properties: `PascalCase` (`StartRecording`, `IsPlaying`).
- Fields: `camelCase`, with leading underscore for serialized private fields (`_handVisualizer`).
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` or `PascalCase` for `static readonly`.
- Prefer `[SerializeField] private` over `public` for inspector fields. Public means "API surface", not "inspector input".
- One MonoBehaviour per file. Filename = class name.
- No `using UnityEditor` outside `Editor/` folders.
- `nullable` is OFF in Unity 2022.3 by default — do not enable it project-wide without ADR.

## Asset workflow

- **Asset Serialization Mode**: Force Text. Verify via `Edit > Project Settings > Editor`. This is mandatory for a 3-person team — binary assets break PR diffs.
- **Version Control Mode**: Visible Meta Files.
- Never commit `Library/`, `Temp/`, `Logs/`, `UserSettings/`, `obj/`, `Build/`, `Builds/`. Already ignored via `.gitignore` — do not unignore.
- Binary assets (PNG, FBX, WAV, MP4, etc.) are routed through Git LFS via `.gitattributes`. Run `git lfs install` once per local clone before committing binaries.
- Scenes / prefabs / assets use the `unityyamlmerge` merge driver. Each teammate registers it once locally — procedure documented in `docs/05-operations/build-deploy.md`.

## Naming conventions for assets

- Scenes: `Scenes/<Area>/<Name>.unity` (e.g. `Scenes/Authoring/Recorder.unity`).
- Prefabs: `Prefabs/<Category>/<Name>.prefab` (e.g. `Prefabs/XR/GhostHand.prefab`).
- ScriptableObjects: `<Type>_<Name>.asset` (e.g. `MasterclassDefinition_TestClass.asset`).
- Materials: `M_<Subject>` (e.g. `M_GhostHand`).
- Textures: `T_<Subject>_<Channel>` (e.g. `T_GhostHand_Albedo`).
- Audio: `A_<Category>_<Name>` (e.g. `A_Voice_TestClass`).

## Scripts folder structure

```
Assets/
  Scripts/
    Authoring/        # expert-side: recording flow
    Playback/         # learner-side: replay flow
    Domain/           # POCOs, value objects, no UnityEngine dependency
    Infrastructure/   # serialization, file IO, networking
    XR/               # XR-specific MonoBehaviours and helpers
    UI/               # in-headset UI
    Editor/           # editor-only tools (any folder named Editor is excluded from runtime build)
    Tests/
      EditMode/
      PlayMode/
```

Keep `Domain/` free of `UnityEngine` references — this enables unit-testable business logic.
